text: Visited Cedele on 11th May, 2.40pm to have a cup of coffee. Members get a complimentary cake on the birthday month and the cashier was really friendly. The ambience is comfortable and relaxing for an afternoon tea break and there are plenty of tables available at this timing.
Visited here for tea break. Staff are friendly wishing us Happy Bday when we bought a slices cake for bday. The matcha cake was good not filling. Will definitely visit here again.

The salad bar is excellent, offering a wide selection of fresh, high-quality ingredients.

Seating is comfortable and the space is clean.
not much to complain about in terms of taste, but just really expensive for what you’re getting. one small sandwich costs around $10-13…

I'm very frustrated after noticed a stand of curly hair after eating half way... Yuck!! Occasionally, the tofu and the quinoa taste off (a bit sour, not fresh anymore), well it's okay... But for this hair in the food, it really pissed me off... Very disappointing... Please check the food properly before consuming... Service was neutral, sometimes slow... Atmosphere is decent...
